    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1TextAbstraction_1_1Hyphenation" kindref="compound">Hyphenation</ref> provides an interface to retrieve possible hyphenation of the text. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This module get the hyphen positions for a word. To get the hyphen positions it needs to load the dictionary for the word language. also it need the word to be send using the correct encoding which can be known using</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1TextAbstraction_1_1Hyphenation_1ad55279c77b67b9735d2038bed68860b1" kindref="member">Hyphenation</ref><sp/>hyphenation<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1TextAbstraction_1_1Hyphenation_1a9ea68a06ec89fd9d1480956a36c564c2" kindref="member">Hyphenation::Get</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1TextAbstraction_1ac95051206fbc2cf8cbe3cef9cb19889f" kindref="member">Character</ref>*<sp/>text<sp/>=<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;Hyphenation&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>get<sp/>a<sp/>vector<sp/>of<sp/>booleans<sp/>that<sp/>indicates<sp/>possible<sp/>hyphen<sp/>locations.</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">Vector&lt;bool&gt;<sp/>*hyphens<sp/>=<sp/>hyphenation.GetWordHyphens(text,<sp/>11,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;en_US&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
